An agent A claimed that the following metal_device_open code violates the MISRA C 2023 rule 2.1.
<misra_rule>
MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.1 is A project shall not contain unreachable code.

</misra_rule>
<target_code>
Here is the original code of metal_device_open.
```c
int metal_device_open(const char *bus_name, const char *dev_name,
		      struct metal_device **device)
{
	struct metal_bus *bus;
	int error;

	if (!bus_name || !strlen(bus_name) ||
	    !dev_name || !strlen(dev_name) ||
	    !device)
		return -EINVAL;

	error = metal_bus_find(bus_name, &bus);
	if (error)
		return error;

	if (!bus->ops.dev_open)
		return -ENODEV;

	error = (*bus->ops.dev_open)(bus, dev_name, device);
	if (error)
		return error;

	return 0;
}
```
